    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date>Novr 28<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. 1858</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><persName>Miss Esther Davidson</persName> of your city who is<lb/>
                an applicant for Governess in my family has referred me<lb/> to you, in a recent
                letter, to testify as to her character &amp;<lb/> capacity, and as the position she
                will occupy is one of<lb/> importance I trust that with your usual frankness
                &amp;<lb/> kindness you will give me full particulars touching<lb/> her character,
                disposition, &amp; capabilities.—</p>
            <p>As she will be the companion of my wife and the Instruc<lb/>tress, of four of my
                children three girls and one boy<lb/> whose ages vary from 12 to 6 years it is
                highly<lb/> important that I should be made acquainted<lb/> with her
                antecedents—</p>
            <p>I am asking to procure the services of a Lady who<lb/> while she is capable of
                teaching the varied <add>?</add><lb/> of an english education can also impart
                lessons<lb/> in French, Music, &amp; Painting, at the same time<lb/> I desire one
                who will also be enabled to cultivate<lb/> the moral sense,—and while she improves
                the<lb/> mind will also train the heart—</p>
            <p>In selecting such a person I should be governed<lb/> in a great measure by the
                credentials of friends<lb/> of the party &amp; if therefore your recommendation of<lb/>
                <persName>Miss Davidson</persName> embodies my views &amp; wishes I<lb/> will take
                great pleasure in securing her</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>services or that of any other person you may<lb/> be pleased to recommend.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Anticipating an early and favourable<lb/> response.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Very respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Your obdt Servt</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">B. Mordecai</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
